We recommended that Management:
a. Instruct the BAC to invite representatives from National Associations of Contractors duly recognized by the Construction Industry Authority of the Philippines as observer in all stages of the procurement of infrastructure projects and to require the BAC, with the assistance of the BAC Secretariat, and TWG, to verify the list of contractor’s equipment together with its availability and operating condition to ensure availability of required equipment during the contract period;
b. Direct the BAC Secretariat to ensure that BAC resolutions are duly signed by the Municipal Mayor and pertinent details of the procurement are consistent in the documents to avoid confusions and see to it that Statement of all Government and Private Contracts and the Statement of All Completed Government and Private Construction Contracts which are similar in nature are supported with CPES rating Sheets and Certificate of Completion and Owner's acceptance as required in item m of Section 12.1 of the Bid Data Sheet and NOA, Contract and NTP, respectively;
c. Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to require the contractor to provide a valid Sales Invoices or ORs for the abovementioned payments and to entail the contractor of the payment of bid document of ₱15,000.00 and to issue additional OR for the deficiency of ₱66,107.99 for the first partial payment made; and
