We recommended that the Local Chief Executive ensure compliance with the procedures provided by existing laws, rules and regulations on property and supply management to present fairly the book value of the PPE in the financial statements by performing the following corrective measures:

Create an Inventory Committee who shall conduct annual physical inventory of all properties and submit copy of the RPCPPE to the auditor concerned not later than January 31 of each year;

Instruct the Property Officer and the Municipal Accountant to maintain complete and updated records and to facilitate the reconciliation of the balances of the PPE; 

Require the accountable offices to immediately inform the concerned officials of the lost, stolen, damaged or destroyed property; and

Take appropriate action against the concerned accountable official/s for non-compliance and repeated unjustified failure to comply with the requirements pursuant to Section 127 of PD 1445.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive ensure compliance with the procedures provided by existing laws, rules and regulations on property and supply management to present fairly the book value of the Property, Plant and Equipment (PPE) in the financial statements by performing the following corrective measures:
Create an Inventory Committee who shall conduct annual physical inventory of all properties and submit copy of the  RPCPPE to the auditor concerned not later than January 31 of each year;
Instruct the Property Officer and the Municipal Accountant to maintain complete and updated records and to facilitate the reconciliation of the balances of the Property, Plant and Equipment (PPE);
Require the accountable offices to immediately inform the concerned officials of the lost, stolen, damaged or destroyed property; and
Take appropriate action against the concerned accountable official/s for non-compliance and repeated unjustified failure to comply with the requirements pursuant to Section 127 of PD 1445.

We have reiterated our recommendation to the management the following courses of action:
Strictly adhere with the pertinent provisions of RA 10121, COA Circular No. 2012-002, DILG Memorandum Circular No. 2012-73 and  NDRRMC-DBM-DILG Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-001 in the management, accounting, recording and utilization of Calamity Fund;
Prepare a Journal Entry Voucher to cause the transfer of the unutilized DRRMF-QRF and MOOE for CY 2015-2016 to the Special Trust Fund under the account “Trust Liability-DRRM” (Account Code 2-04-01-020) in the Trust Fund Book;
Maintain separate registry of appropriations, allotments and obligations (RAAO) for QRF, MOOE and CO;
Maintain subsidiary ledgers for transfers of agency’s unutilized DRRMF to the Special Trust Fund by year of transfer.
Instruct the Local Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Officer (LDRRMO) as well as the Municipal Accountant to prepare and submit the monthly certified correct Report on Sources and Utilization of DRRMF; and
Maximize the utilization of the LDRRMF in accordance with the LDRRMFIP for the proper implementation of actions and measures for the reduction of all aspects of disaster risk reduction, risk assessment and early warning and preparedness for effective response and early recovery as provided with the pertinent provisions of laws, rules and regulations on calamity fund.

a. We have recommended to the management the following courses of action:

•	Strictly adhere with the provisions of RA 10121 and COA Circular No. 2012-002 dated September 12, 2012 in the management and recording of Calamity Fund;

•	Instruct the Municipal Accountant to prepare and submit the monthly certified correct Report on Sources and Utilization of DRRMF; and

•	Prepare LDRRMFIP to be approved by the LDRRMC as required under the existing rules and regulations.

b. We have recommended that management:

•	Strictly adhere with the provisions of RA 10121 and COA Circular No. 2012-002 dated September 12, 2012 in the accounting and recording of Calamity Fund;

•	Prepare a Journal Entry Voucher to cause the transfer of the unutilized DRRMF-QRF and MOOE for CY 2013-2015 to the Special Trust Fund under the account “Trust Liability-DRRM” (Account Code 438/2-04-01-020) in the Trust Fund Books;

•	Maintain separate registry of appropriations, allotments and obligations (RAAO) for QRF, MOOE and CO;

•	Ensure that all unexpended/unobligated balance of the LDRRMF for CO shall be made continuing in the General Fund books until the projects funded therefore are completed and any savings shall be available for use in the disaster risk reduction management activities as provided in the LDRRMFIP; and

•	Maintain subsidiary ledgers for transfers of agency’s unutilized DRRMF to the Special Trust Fund by year of transfer.
